text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia ascendens is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to a small area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The erect shrub typically grows to a height of 1.3 to 3 metres (4 to 10 ft). It blooms from June to September and produces yellow flowers.
